    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="Switching sources" class="article-title">
          Switching sources
          
        </h1>

      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><h2>How to switch sources basically</h2>
<p>Once your sources are hooked up, you can switch between therm during your live performance in a very simple way.<br>Simply select the desired source, it will then switch to preview mode, recognizable by the green light that will appear on it.<br>If you want to select it for live, click on "apply". The light will turn red, and the source you have selected will be the one used for Live.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="wysiwyg-text-align-center"><img src="../article_attachments/360019170380/Swap_Gif.gif" alt="Swap_Gif.gif"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3><span class="wysiwyg-underline">Dazzl Tips</span></h3>
<p>You can also switch modes by clicking this button in the upper right corner of the screen:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="wysiwyg-text-align-center"><img src="../article_attachments/360008096400/Screen_Shot_2020-01-17_at_12.47.58.png" alt="Screen_Shot_2020-01-17_at_12.47.58.png"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Your scre<span>en will then be displayed like this:</span></p>
<p><img src="../article_attachments/360008106919/Source_2.gif" alt="Source_2.gif"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>By using this mode, you will still have a preview: the source you click on will be selected and you will have to swap it to live.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
          
        </div>
      </section>

